50|$|The Irish Defence Forces are {{assigned}} {{from time to}} time to carry out search and rescue operations. Ireland's special forces, the Army Ranger Wing have been used for search and rescue operations in difficult or dangerous operations on land and at sea. The Irish Naval Service frequently assists the other agencies in search and rescue. Its patrol ships at sea and the communications center at Haulbowline maintain a 24-hour watch on all <b>distress</b> <b>frequencies.</b> The Irish Air Corps are used for rescue and provide top cover for search and rescue over land or sea.|$|R
